1
00:00:14,900 --> 00:00:16,667
Our baby's alive, Red!

2
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:18,467
I knew it.

3
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:19,567
Yen, I'm sorry.

4
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:21,967
Sorry for convincing
you to move on.

5
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:24,100
I thought our baby was gone.

6
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:26,067
We don't deserve this.

7
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:28,200
I wonder how Chloe's doing.

8
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:29,333
What are they feeding her?

9
00:00:29,467 --> 00:00:31,767
What kind of milk are they
giving her?

10
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:34,867
She's been separated from us
for several months now.

11
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:37,000
I'm sure she's just like you.

12
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:41,667
What matters is that
we can get her back now.

13
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,833
She will be with you soon.

14
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:47,267
I hated you before because
I believed

15
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:50,267
that you were the reason
my daughter died.

16
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:53,933
That's the opportunity Rina
was waiting

17
00:00:54,067 --> 00:00:56,433
to ruin our relationship.

18
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,267
I'm sorry.

19
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:00,167
I'm sorry, Mom.

20
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:08,633
Red, this is not the place
where they took me.

21
00:01:08,967 --> 00:01:10,433
I asked around.

22
00:01:10,767 --> 00:01:12,733
They said Thelma always
moves around.

23
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:14,300
This is where she lives now.

24
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:15,600
Mom!

25
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,500
Our baby's not here.

26
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:23,067
I want to stay hopeful.
But it seems so hard.

27
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:26,167
We can't give up, Yen.
For our child's sake.

28
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:28,367
For Chloe.

29
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:29,600
Hello?

30
00:01:29,733 --> 00:01:30,667
Hello?

31
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:31,900
It's Mom.

32
00:01:35,833 --> 00:01:37,333
Mom, where's our baby?

33
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:39,667
Don't get too excited.

34
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:42,500
- My baby!
- Don't hurt her!

35
00:01:42,667 --> 00:01:45,467
Rina, don't harm the baby!

36
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:46,433
Who is that?

37
00:01:46,567 --> 00:01:48,333
Is that Amanda? Amanda?

38
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:50,867
Amanda, hello!

39
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,300
Don't hurt our baby!

40
00:01:53,433 --> 00:01:56,833
Well, you know it's all up
to you, Eden.

41
00:01:56,967 --> 00:02:01,767
I won't hurt your baby if you do
everything I say.

42
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:04,000
I will give you everything
you want.

43
00:02:04,133 --> 00:02:07,633
Just don't hurt our baby!
Give her back!

44
00:02:07,767 --> 00:02:10,000
Everything?

45
00:02:10,133 --> 00:02:12,333
Do you promise?

46
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:14,300
Will you give me everything
I ask for?

47
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:15,833
Will you do everything I say?

48
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:18,000
Fine.

49
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:22,700
I will give your baby back if...

50
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:28,200
you give me your mother.

51
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:33,367
Give me Amanda in exchange
for your daughter.

52
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,667
Deal?

53
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:44,067
You're crazy!

54
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,267
You must be out of your mind
to think

55
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,667
that I will hand you my wife!

56
00:02:47,833 --> 00:02:48,333
No way!

57
00:02:48,467 --> 00:02:49,600
Oh, shut up, Lucho!

58
00:02:49,733 --> 00:02:51,867
I have the upper hand
right now

59
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:57,233
because I have something
very valuable to you.

60
00:02:57,367 --> 00:02:58,667
Mom...

61
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:00,967
Mom, please.

62
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:04,067
Please give us our baby back.

63
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,000
Don't you care about me anymore?

64
00:03:06,133 --> 00:03:07,533
Is that why you're doing this
to me?

65
00:03:07,667 --> 00:03:09,333
You too, Red!

66
00:03:09,467 --> 00:03:12,833
Didn't you abandon me too?

67
00:03:12,967 --> 00:03:16,967
You made me feel like
I'm worthless to you!

68
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:18,300
Rina, Rina.

69
00:03:18,433 --> 00:03:19,800
Please, surrender.

70
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:22,000
We'll help you. I'll help you!

71
00:03:22,167 --> 00:03:23,033
You, too!
You're a liar!

72
00:03:24,167 --> 00:03:25,867
You abandoned me too!

73
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:29,133
So all of you will feel
my wrath!

74
00:03:31,567 --> 00:03:34,300
Enough of this drama, please!
Okay?

75
00:03:34,433 --> 00:03:41,267
Bring Amanda to me in exchange
of this baby.

76
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,933
And don't even try to call
the police.

77
00:03:44,067 --> 00:03:46,000
Because I will find out.

78
00:03:46,133 --> 00:03:48,933
You will be in more trouble.

79
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:57,433
So, bring Amanda here
to Zandro's hideout.

80
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,733
At 6 PM.

81
00:03:59,867 --> 00:04:03,667
Baby and I will be waiting.

82
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:06,967
Please, leave the child out
of this.

83
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:12,800
Right, baby?

84
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:17,467
Shut up!

85
00:04:18,867 --> 00:04:20,800
My baby, Red!

86
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:33,300
I said, shut up!

87
00:04:33,433 --> 00:04:35,100
Shut up!

88
00:04:38,133 --> 00:04:40,000
Are you hungry?

89
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:46,000
Are you tired, baby?

90
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:49,900
Well, I don't care.

91
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:54,033
They say you're my grandchild.

92
00:04:54,967 --> 00:04:57,267
You have Amanda's blood!

93
00:04:58,767 --> 00:05:00,967
You're worthless to me.

94
00:05:01,133 --> 00:05:02,933
Do you understand?

95
00:05:10,433 --> 00:05:12,533
Shut up.

96
00:05:13,667 --> 00:05:15,300
Shut up.

97
00:05:16,133 --> 00:05:18,367
Shut up, baby.

98
00:05:20,533 --> 00:05:22,633
Shut up.

99
00:05:23,967 --> 00:05:28,600
You're just a means to an end.

100
00:05:30,933 --> 00:05:33,067
You're worthless to me.

101
00:05:46,067 --> 00:05:48,567
I'm sorry the subscribers cannot
be reached.

102
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:50,167
Please try again later.

103
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:53,067
I can't contact her anymore.

104
00:05:55,233 --> 00:05:56,167
We have no choice.

105
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:58,133
We have to alert the police.

106
00:05:59,100 --> 00:05:59,600
You can't!

107
00:05:59,733 --> 00:06:01,233
That's a good idea.

108
00:06:01,367 --> 00:06:04,033
We should let the police deal
with your mom.

109
00:06:04,167 --> 00:06:06,233
No! You can't report her
to the police!

110
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:08,000
She might hurt Chloe!

111
00:06:08,167 --> 00:06:09,267
She's just saying that.

112
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,967
But once the police officers
get there,

113
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:12,033
she can't do anything anymore.

114
00:06:12,167 --> 00:06:13,867
Your mom will be captured.

115
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,367
What if it doesn't end that way?

116
00:06:17,967 --> 00:06:20,133
You heard her, right?

117
00:06:20,267 --> 00:06:22,667
She seems out of her mind.

118
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:25,033
I don't want to upset her
any further.

119
00:06:25,167 --> 00:06:27,033
She might harm the baby.

120
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:33,767
If we're not going to call
the police, what do we do then?

121
00:06:36,467 --> 00:06:38,200
I'll handle it.

122
00:06:39,233 --> 00:06:40,867
I'll talk to her.

123
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,133
I'm still her son.

124
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:45,333
She's mad at you, remember?

125
00:06:45,467 --> 00:06:48,067
How can you be so sure
that she'll listen to you?

126
00:06:49,233 --> 00:06:51,600
She might be mad at me
earlier over the phone.

127
00:06:51,733 --> 00:06:56,233
But once she sees me in person,
she might change her mind.

128
00:06:57,233 --> 00:06:58,900
Son, son.

129
00:06:59,033 --> 00:07:00,533
Dindi's right.

130
00:07:00,667 --> 00:07:04,467
At this state, she might not
listen to you.

131
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:07,867
I'm afraid of what she can do
to you.

132
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,567
I'll come with Red.

133
00:07:10,700 --> 00:07:12,767
We'll talk to her.

134
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:17,300
You can't talk sense
into her anymore.

135
00:07:17,467 --> 00:07:20,500
She chose to use violence.
We can do the same!

136
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,167
And then what?

137
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:25,067
Are we going to corner her?

138
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:27,067
What if she hurts the child?

139
00:07:28,933 --> 00:07:33,100
We're not sure if she'll give us
the child.

140
00:07:33,233 --> 00:07:37,933
What if she kills the baby
no matter what we do?

141
00:07:38,067 --> 00:07:39,833
Please, don't talk like that!

142
00:07:41,667 --> 00:07:45,833
Eden, I'm sorry. But I know
how she thinks.

143
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,333
Don't be like that.

144
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,633
Why are you making us lose hope?

145
00:07:51,767 --> 00:07:54,233
We haven't seen Chloe yet.

146
00:07:55,167 --> 00:07:56,900
I'm just being realistic.

147
00:07:57,033 --> 00:07:58,167
Stop.

148
00:07:58,300 --> 00:08:00,433
That's enough! You don't need
to argue.

149
00:08:00,567 --> 00:08:02,700
There's only one solution
to this problem.

150
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:06,633
I will go to Rina.

151
00:08:06,767 --> 00:08:12,167
We'll give her what she wants
in exchange for your child.

152
00:08:23,567 --> 00:08:25,467
Mom, you don't need to do that.

153
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:28,167
It's the only way.

154
00:08:31,967 --> 00:08:34,033
I won't let you do it.

155
00:08:34,167 --> 00:08:36,033
Lucho.

156
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:40,133
Amanda, I can't let you
put yourself in danger.

157
00:08:41,967 --> 00:08:43,533
He's right, Amanda.

158
00:08:43,667 --> 00:08:47,333
And we all know what Rina
wants to do to you.

159
00:08:47,467 --> 00:08:48,933
She's not doing this

160
00:08:49,067 --> 00:08:51,033
so she can have a conversation
with you.

161
00:08:51,167 --> 00:08:52,167
She will kill you!

162
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:53,733
Then she can go ahead
and kill me!

163
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:55,367
Mom!

164
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,667
Mom, don't talk like that.
Let's think of another way.

165
00:08:58,800 --> 00:08:59,667
Not like this.

166
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:02,967
I don't want anyone to get hurt,
Mom.

167
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:05,100
But we can't find another way.

168
00:09:05,233 --> 00:09:07,400
This is the only way.

169
00:09:08,633 --> 00:09:11,833
This is the only way to get
your child back.

170
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:16,100
It's all my fault anyway.

171
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:21,000
This feud started because
I fought back with Rina.

172
00:09:22,167 --> 00:09:25,000
This is our feud.
We started this.

173
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:27,533
So we have to end
this ourselves.

174
00:09:28,933 --> 00:09:33,733
This wouldn't get this far
if I hadn't been so selfish...

175
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:36,833
if I didn't play her game...

176
00:09:36,967 --> 00:09:38,267
if I didn't take revenge.

177
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,933
So let me do this.

178
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:47,400
Let me make up for what I did.

179
00:09:47,533 --> 00:09:49,333
Mom!

180
00:09:49,467 --> 00:09:50,667
I've made a decision.

181
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,700
You can't change my mind.

182
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:55,400
The two of you should prepare

183
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:58,033
because you're about to get your
baby back.

184
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:00,433
- Mom!
- Amanda.

185
00:10:02,467 --> 00:10:03,367
Amanda.

186
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,767
Mom, I can't let you do this.

187
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:09,167
Mom! I can't let you do this!

188
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:11,500
I'm scared for your life.

189
00:10:11,633 --> 00:10:13,133
I want us to be together.

190
00:10:13,267 --> 00:10:15,133
I want to be with you,
with Red and baby Chloe.

191
00:10:15,267 --> 00:10:16,800
I can't let you do this, Mom!

192
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:18,533
Yen, I'm sorry, it's my fault

193
00:10:18,667 --> 00:10:21,400
that you don't have
a complete family.

194
00:10:21,533 --> 00:10:23,167
No, Mom!

195
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,333
If only I'd forgiven Rina

196
00:10:26,467 --> 00:10:29,067
and moved on with my life
with Lucho,

197
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:32,067
this wouldn't have happened.

198
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:34,767
Mom, it's Rina
who can't forgive.

199
00:10:34,933 --> 00:10:36,633
Not you.

200
00:10:36,767 --> 00:10:38,000
She might be acting like this

201
00:10:38,133 --> 00:10:40,467
because I didn't ask her
for forgiveness.

202
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:44,900
Eden, even if I didn't kill
her son,

203
00:10:45,033 --> 00:10:47,300
I failed to protect Angelo.

204
00:10:47,433 --> 00:10:49,833
That's why Rina got hurt.

205
00:10:51,233 --> 00:10:52,800
I will talk to her.

206
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:55,033
I'll talk to her and ask
for her forgiveness.

207
00:10:55,167 --> 00:10:57,433
I'll ask her to stop
getting revenge.

208
00:10:57,567 --> 00:10:59,900
So no one else can get hurt
anymore.

209
00:11:04,533 --> 00:11:07,233
Mom, what if she doesn't listen
to you?

210
00:11:13,133 --> 00:11:17,433
I'm willing to give my life
in exchange for your child.

211
00:11:20,767 --> 00:11:23,233
Maybe that's what I need to do.

212
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:28,033
This is what I need to do
so we can all have peace.

213
00:11:46,533 --> 00:11:48,600
Get my gun ready.

214
00:11:48,867 --> 00:11:50,567
Yes, boss.

215
00:11:51,633 --> 00:11:53,133
What are you planning to do?

216
00:11:53,433 --> 00:11:55,233
Are you going to have
a gunfight with my mom?

217
00:11:56,267 --> 00:11:57,900
What do you expect me to do?

218
00:11:58,900 --> 00:12:01,133
Do you think I'll just let Rina
take my wife?

219
00:12:01,267 --> 00:12:03,867
What if Chloe gets hurt?

220
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,267
Amanda is all I care about
right now!

221
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:10,167
I will kill for her!

222
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:16,167
You don't need to do that,
Lucho.

223
00:12:17,267 --> 00:12:21,433
Amanda, you can't make me
useless.

224
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:24,800
I can't let you risk your life!

225
00:12:24,933 --> 00:12:26,733
I need to protect you!

226
00:12:27,633 --> 00:12:29,600
I know what you want to do.

227
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:34,067
You don't need to kill anyone
for me.

228
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:39,100
Lucho, I'm grateful to you.

229
00:12:40,267 --> 00:12:41,533
For everything that you've
given me.

230
00:12:41,667 --> 00:12:43,467
You've given me a new life.

231
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,533
You support everything
I want to do.

232
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:47,067
But that's enough.

233
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,033
Our revenge ends today.

234
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:53,367
We have to stop using violence.
It won't do us anything good.

235
00:12:54,467 --> 00:12:59,200
Look at what happened.
The child's life is in danger.

236
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:01,300
So, what do you want to do?

237
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:02,900
Are you going to face Rina
alone?

238
00:13:05,567 --> 00:13:07,500
Is that okay with you?

239
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:10,833
Do all of you think it's okay?!

240
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,667
You have to let me do this.

241
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:23,233
I will talk to Rina. I will ask
for her forgiveness.

242
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:31,533
I will come back to you if
God listens to my prayers.

243
00:13:34,133 --> 00:13:38,400
I will come home to you.
We will have a complete family.

244
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:29,467
Red.

245
00:14:33,133 --> 00:14:35,467
Have you talked
to your mom already?

246
00:14:37,667 --> 00:14:39,633
I couldn't change her mind.

247
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:42,067
She said she would give her life

248
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:44,767
so our family could be together.

249
00:14:46,667 --> 00:14:49,033
Do we need to get this far?

250
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:54,567
If only I could do it instead
of her.

251
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:58,100
I'm also willing to give my life
for our child.

252
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:02,467
Can't we get her back
without anyone getting hurt?

253
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:12,967
I only want simple things
in life.

254
00:15:14,633 --> 00:15:16,800
I just want our family
to be together.

255
00:15:19,167 --> 00:15:21,267
Why does it seem so hard to get?

256
00:15:24,467 --> 00:15:27,400
We can't let Auntie Amanda
risk her life.

257
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:31,333
I will try to talk to my mom.

258
00:15:33,967 --> 00:15:39,967
She thinks we abandoned her.

259
00:15:42,267 --> 00:15:45,800
So if I have to kneel
in front of her

260
00:15:45,933 --> 00:15:50,733
to ask for forgiveness, I will.

261
00:15:50,867 --> 00:15:52,000
Red.

262
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:58,933
Yen, I don't want my mom
to become a murderer.

263
00:16:01,267 --> 00:16:03,700
She's done a lot of bad things
already.

264
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:08,267
I don't want her to commit
more crimes.

265
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:18,633
Red, I know you want
to save your mom.

266
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:23,867
I know that you don't want her
to get hurt.

267
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:27,200
I understand.

268
00:16:29,233 --> 00:16:34,067
I also don't want anything bad
to happen to her.

269
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:44,033
But we both know she has to pay
for everything she's done.

270
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,800
Mom, answer the phone, please.

271
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:43,767
I thought I was going die
on that island.

272
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:46,000
I thought I wouldn't
see you again.

273
00:17:46,133 --> 00:17:48,233
No, don't say that, son.

274
00:17:49,033 --> 00:17:51,100
You know...

275
00:17:51,233 --> 00:17:53,567
God is so good.

276
00:17:54,467 --> 00:17:56,233
He's so good.

277
00:17:56,367 --> 00:17:59,667
He won't let that happen to us.

278
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:04,833
We still have a lot of plans
to travel abroad.

279
00:18:04,967 --> 00:18:08,800
You still have a lot of dreams
to achieve.

280
00:18:08,933 --> 00:18:11,900
We're always here for you, son.

281
00:18:12,033 --> 00:18:13,133
I'm back!

282
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:17,433
My son!

283
00:18:19,033 --> 00:18:20,967
I'm not going anywhere.

284
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,700
I'm not going to leave you
again.

285
00:18:22,867 --> 00:18:25,000
I will continue my studies here.

286
00:18:25,133 --> 00:18:27,400
A hundred percent! I will
take care of you.

287
00:18:27,533 --> 00:18:28,933
I'm staying here. I'm not
going anywhere.

288
00:18:29,067 --> 00:18:31,467
I'm not sick.

289
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:35,367
It will be better for you
to stay in the US.

290
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:37,267
No.

291
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:40,767
I'll stay here with you
and dad, okay?

292
00:18:42,133 --> 00:18:44,900
You're so stubborn!

293
00:18:45,033 --> 00:18:46,433
Of course, where do you think
I got it from?

294
00:18:46,567 --> 00:18:48,200
I got it from you!

295
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:50,667
Now that I'm here...

296
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:53,067
I'm going to make you laugh
every day.

297
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:55,567
I'm going to make you happy.

298
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:58,333
I miss you, son.

299
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:01,100
I miss you so much.

300
00:19:05,233 --> 00:19:06,700
There are a lot of women
out there.

301
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,967
Yenyen is just one of them.

302
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:10,333
You talked to Amanda,
didn't you?

303
00:19:10,467 --> 00:19:12,633
She put those ideas
in your head!

304
00:19:12,767 --> 00:19:14,200
Right? Am I right?

305
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:18,767
That woman was sentenced
to jail because she was guilty!

306
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:22,000
You're the child of the woman
who killed my son!

307
00:19:22,133 --> 00:19:23,133
- Mom!
- You wench!

308
00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:24,600
And now you're going
to take my other child!

309
00:19:24,733 --> 00:19:25,700
Mom, stop!

310
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:27,100
- Stay away from my son!
- Mom!

311
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:29,233
- Stay away from him!
- Mom!

312
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:32,133
This is the only time
I will tell you this!

313
00:19:32,367 --> 00:19:35,300
Stay away from Eden, or else!

314
00:19:40,567 --> 00:19:41,767
Red?

315
00:20:09,867 --> 00:20:11,333
I'm sorry.

316
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:17,800
I don't know how things ended up
this way.

317
00:20:19,733 --> 00:20:21,333
Red.

318
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,433
I know she loved me.

319
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:32,267
She took care of me.

320
00:20:35,167 --> 00:20:38,000
How could she hurt me like this?

321
00:20:40,833 --> 00:20:43,533
I took her side, Yen.
I took her side.

322
00:20:46,633 --> 00:20:48,600
I took her side.

323
00:20:50,767 --> 00:20:52,800
She betrayed me.

324
00:20:52,933 --> 00:20:55,467
How could she do this to me?

325
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:58,500
Why did she do this to me?

326
00:21:02,433 --> 00:21:04,200
Red...

327
00:21:29,167 --> 00:21:30,300
Lucho?

328
00:21:31,933 --> 00:21:33,700
Where are you going?

329
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:40,833
Are you going somewhere?

330
00:21:47,700 --> 00:21:50,100
I can't do it, Dindi.

331
00:21:52,067 --> 00:21:57,100
I can't let Amanda deal
with that crazy woman alone.

332
00:21:58,467 --> 00:22:02,133
You know what Rina did
to the midwife.

333
00:22:02,267 --> 00:22:07,667
What else can she do once
she sees her mortal enemy?

334
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:10,167
But what about the baby?

335
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:14,100
She might get hurt
if you get involved.

336
00:22:16,467 --> 00:22:18,067
What about Amanda?

337
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:21,300
She's my wife.

338
00:22:21,433 --> 00:22:22,633
She's my only concern.

339
00:22:22,767 --> 00:22:24,967
Lucho, please.

340
00:22:26,833 --> 00:22:29,133
I love Amanda so much, Dindi.

341
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:33,900
I waited a long time for her.

342
00:22:34,033 --> 00:22:37,033
I thought we would never
be together.

343
00:22:37,167 --> 00:22:39,567
But fate made us cross paths
again.

344
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:44,300
I still can't believe
that she's my wife now.

345
00:22:46,133 --> 00:22:50,733
That's why I will do everything
to defend her.

346
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:53,267
To protect her.

347
00:22:54,500 --> 00:22:57,300
I can't lose her, Dindi.

348
00:22:57,433 --> 00:22:59,700
I won't let that happen.

349
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:02,633
I don't want her to get hurt,
either.

350
00:23:03,867 --> 00:23:08,733
Because she'd been through
so much to survive.

351
00:23:08,867 --> 00:23:11,767
This can't end like this!

352
00:23:19,033 --> 00:23:21,700
Go on.

353
00:23:24,833 --> 00:23:26,567
Go and follow them.

354
00:23:28,433 --> 00:23:31,000
But please, Lucho.

355
00:23:31,133 --> 00:23:34,067
Bring my sister home alive.

356
00:24:19,333 --> 00:24:21,667
Mom, no one should get hurt.

357
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:23,000
You can be free again.

358
00:24:23,133 --> 00:24:24,267
No! Free?

359
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:25,333
Me?

360
00:24:25,467 --> 00:24:27,200
I will have to run all my life.

361
00:24:27,333 --> 00:24:28,967
Because the police will be
looking for me.

362
00:24:29,133 --> 00:24:30,433
That's what's going
to happen to me.

363
00:24:30,567 --> 00:24:33,867
But you know what,
I don't mind.

364
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:36,467
As long as I get my revenge
for Angelo.

365
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:38,867
I'm begging you.

366
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:41,100
Please save her again.

367
00:24:41,233 --> 00:24:44,167
Save our family.

368
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,267
I won't let you win, Rina.

369
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:48,733
I can't let you have Amanda.

370
00:24:48,867 --> 00:24:50,133
Run! Amanda!

371
00:24:50,867 --> 00:24:51,733
Our baby!

372
00:24:51,867 --> 00:24:53,000
Lucho!

373
00:24:53,133 --> 00:24:54,800
The baby!
